.TH "bd70528_wdt_lock" 9 "bd70528_wdt_lock" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bd70528_wdt_lock \- take WDT lock
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" bd70528_wdt_lock
.BI "(struct rohm_regmap_dev *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
device data for the PMIC instance we want to operate on
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Lock WDT for arming/disarming in order to avoid race condition caused
by WDT state changes initiated by WDT and RTC drivers.
